# =============================================================================
# Sprintly — .dockerignore
# =============================================================================
#
# WHY this file matters:
#   When you run "docker build" or "docker-compose up --build", Docker first
#   tars up the entire build context (the directory containing this file)
#   and sends it to the Docker daemon. Without .dockerignore, it sends
#   EVERYTHING — including target/ folders (compiled JARs, hundreds of MB),
#   .git history, IDE files, logs.
#
#   This slows down every build significantly and can leak sensitive files
#   into the build context. .dockerignore works exactly like .gitignore:
#   listed patterns are excluded from the context sent to the daemon.
#
# Impact:
#   Without .dockerignore: build context ~500MB+ (all target/ folders)
#   With .dockerignore:    build context ~5MB  (only source files + poms)
# =============================================================================

# ── Compiled output ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are the biggest folders — exclude them completely.
# Docker will compile fresh from source inside the builder stage.
**/target/
**/*.class
**/*.jar
**/*.war

# ── Git ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Git history can be large and is never needed in a container
.git/
.gitignore

# ── IDE files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
*.iws
*.ipr
.project
.classpath
.settings/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# ── OS files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/

# ── Environment files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Never bake secrets into Docker images
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# ── Docker files themselves ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Not needed inside the container
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.dockerignore

# ── Documentation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Not needed at runtime
README.md
*.md
docs/

# ── Test reports ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/surefire-reports/
**/failsafe-reports/